  "html": "<h1>What to Check For</h1>\n  <p>Ensure that your application restricts authentication cookies&amp;nbsp;to only&amp;nbsp;HTTPS connections by using the requireSSL attribute.</p>\n  <h1>Why</h1>\n  <p>By using TLS, you prevent an attacker from reading a captured authentication cookie&amp;nbsp;and gaining spoofed access to your application.</p>\n  <h1>How to Fix</h1>\n  <p>Set the <b>secure</b> property of the authentication cookie to ensure that browsers only send authentication cookies over HTTPS connections. </p>\n  <p>Set the <b>secure</b> property by using <b>requireSSL=\"true\"</b> on the &lt;<b>forms</b>&gt; element as shown here:</p>\n  <div>\n    <pre>&lt;forms loginUrl=\"Secure\\Login.aspx\"<br />        requireSSL=\"true\" ... /&gt;</pre>\n  </div>\n  <hr />\n  <p>Adapted from Microsoft patterns &amp; practices guidance. </p>"
